============
FORM: 'CONK'
============

The CONK form is a wrapper for the various ConKit chunk types.

======
CHUNKS
======

'MAP '     (BC, 15/5/94)
========================

For storage of background blockmaps.
format:

UWORD width
UWORD height
UWORD data[width][height]


'BLKS'     (BC, 15/5/94)
========================

Block image data. Blocks assumed to be 1 word wide, 16 lines high, and 1-8
bitplanes deep.

struct BLKSHeader
{
	UWORD	blks_NumOfBlocks;
	UWORD blks_Depth;
};

Followed by interleaved, raw imagedata.

'CMAP'     (BC, 15/5/94)
========================

Palette chunk. Same as CMAP chunk found in ILBM files, ie RGB byte triplets.

